name: Parablarinella latimaxillata
description: The Anhui short-tailed shrew is a species of shrew described in 2023. It is endemic to the Dabie Mountains, China, and only known from its type locality, Yaoluoping Nature Reserve in Anhui where it occurs in broad-leaf deciduous forests at elevations of 1,100–1,700 m (3,600–5,600 ft) above sea level.
